Enumeration\"},{\"DefaultValue\":\"Aut\",\"UefiNamespaceId\":\"x-UEFI-AMI\",\"DisplayName\":\"Device power-up delay\",\"HelpText\":\"Maximum time the device will take before it properly reports itself to the Host Controller. 'Auto' uses default value: for a Root port it is 100 ms, for a Hub port the delay is taken from Hub descriptor.\",\"AttributeName\":\"USB00B\",\"Value\":[{\"ValueName\":\"USB00BAuto\",\"ValueDisplayName\":\"Auto\"},{\"ValueName\":\"USB00BManual\",\"ValueDisplayName\":\"Manual\"}],\"ReadOnly\":false,\"ResetRequired\":true,\"Type\":\"Enumeration\"},{\"DefaultValue\":5,\"ScalarIncrement\":1,\"UefiNamespaceId\":\"x-UEFI-AMI\",\"UpperBound\":40,\"HelpText\":\"Delay range is 1..40 seconds, in one second increments\",\"AttributeName\":\"USB00C\",\"LowerBound\":1,\"ReadOnly\":false,\"ResetRequired\":true,\"Type\":\"Integer\",\"DisplayName\":\"Device power-up delay in seconds\"},{\"DefaultValue\":\"Aut\",\"UefiNamespaceId\":\"x-UEFI-AMI\",\"DisplayName\":\"N\\/A\",\"HelpText\":\"Mass storage device emulation type. 'AUTO' enumerates devices according to their media format. Optical drives are emulated as 'CDROM', drives with no media will be emulated according to a drive type.\",\"AttributeName\":\"USB011\",\"Value\":[{\"ValueName\":\"USB011Auto\",\"ValueDisplayName\":\"Auto\"},{\"ValueName\":\"USB011Floppy\",\"ValueDisplayName\":\"Floppy\"},{\"ValueName\":\"USB011ForcedFDD\",\"ValueDisplayName\":\"Forced FDD\"},{\"ValueName\":\"USB011HardDisk\",\"ValueDisplayName\":\"Hard Disk\"},{\"ValueName\":\"USB011CDROM\",\"ValueDisplayName\":\"CD-ROM\"}],\"ReadOnly\":false,\"ResetRequired\":true,\"Type\":\"Enumeration\"},{\"DefaultValue\":\"Aut\",\"UefiNamespaceId\":\"x-UEFI-AMI\",\"DisplayName\":\"N\\/A\",\"HelpText\":\"Mass storage device emulation type. 'AUTO' enumerates devices according to their media format. Optical drives are emulated as 'CDROM', drives with no media will be emulated according to a drive type.\",\"AttributeName\":\"USB012\",\"Value\":[{\"Valu